						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: 15th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The stone is broken and some of the letters are lost. This record registers a gift of one <hi rend="italic">Khaṇḍuga</hi> of wet land by Timmappa Nāyaka for the service of god Tiruvēṅgaḷanātha, made over to Krushṇadāsa, son of Balavatadēva. The gifted land was situated in Dādalūr-sthaḷa.</p>						

						</summary>
